<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="271" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1230,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rajan &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan &amp; Binoy, 2021" authorityName="Rajan &amp; Kumar &amp; Sureshan &amp; Binoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[336,560,1230,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Spilomena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsunekii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[336,560,1230,1256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Spilomena tsunekii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[568,663,1230,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[568,663,1230,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from its congeners by the following combination of characters: frons and vertex imbricate, without setigerous micropunctures; mesopleuron finely aciculate, with illdefined punctures; relative length to breadth of scape = 20:5; stigma not elongate, relative length to breadth = 98:68; propodeal dorsum transversely striate, with two longitudinal carinae medially, posterior surface finely aciculate, with median longitudinal carina, lateral surface transversely striate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="272" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" box="[199,1076,1410,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1410,1436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[361,471,1410,1436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[478,503,1411,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[668,762,1410,1437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
; fore wing length 
<quantity box="[978,1071,1410,1437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="271" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,291,1446,1473]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Colour.</emphasis>
Body black except pronotum yellowish brown; clypeus and metasoma brown; mandible (except apical tip brown), tegula, pronotal lobe, legs and antenna yellow; fore wing veins and stigma brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" box="[199,1289,1518,1545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1518,1544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Vestiture.</emphasis>
T5–T7 with scattered setigerous punctures; remaining body with sparse vestiture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,271,1554,1581]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Clypeus dull without any appressed setae, markedly convex (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1110,1554,1580]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–44" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1664,1688]" captionTargetBox="[158,1419,187,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-104@10.[151,1424,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37–44. Spilomena tsunekii Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar, sp. nov., Holotype ♂. 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Head, frontal view; 39. Head and mesosoma (in part), dorsal view; 40. Mesosoma, lateral view; 41. Propodeum, dorsal view; 42. Metasoma, dorsal view; 43. Fore wing; 44. Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704393/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
); interantennal tubercle inconspicuous, not distinctly pointed, extending into short median carina at most reaching lower frons; mandible bidentate, inner mandibular tooth short, blunt; relative length to breadth of scape =20:5 frons and vertex imbricate without setigerous micropunctures; inner eye margin straight; gena imbricate, impunctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1976]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,1698,1725]" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pronotum reticulate, with irregular longitudinal rugae; anterior carina of pronotal collar conspicuous, deeply emarginate; mesoscutum reticulate, with scattered setigerous punctures; admedian line and parapsidal line lacking; scutellum dull and reticulate, with sparse setigerous punctures, anterior groove of scutellum not broadened by crenulation; metanotum dull and reticulate, irregularly transversely rugose laterally; mesopleuron finely aciculate, with ill-defined punctures (
<figureCitation box="[569,654,1842,1868]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–44" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1664,1688]" captionTargetBox="[158,1419,187,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-104@10.[151,1424,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37–44. Spilomena tsunekii Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar, sp. nov., Holotype ♂. 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Head, frontal view; 39. Head and mesosoma (in part), dorsal view; 40. Mesosoma, lateral view; 41. Propodeum, dorsal view; 42. Metasoma, dorsal view; 43. Fore wing; 44. Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704393/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
); metapleuron finely aciculate; stigma not elongate, relative length to breadth = 98:68; recurrent vein of fore wing received well within first submarginal cell; propodeal dorsum transversely striate, with two longitudinal carinae medially, posterior surface finely aciculate, with median longitudinal carina (
<figureCitation box="[235,318,1950,1976]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–44" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1664,1688]" captionTargetBox="[158,1419,187,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-104@10.[151,1424,181,1645]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 37–44. Spilomena tsunekii Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar, sp. nov., Holotype ♂. 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Head, frontal view; 39. Head and mesosoma (in part), dorsal view; 40. Mesosoma, lateral view; 41. Propodeum, dorsal view; 42. Metasoma, dorsal view; 43. Fore wing; 44. Hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704393/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="271">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
), lateral surface transversely striate.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704391" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5704391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704391/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="272" startId="9.[151,264,1677,1701]" targetBox="[159,1420,193,1648]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1677,1773]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,341,1677,1701]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">FIGURES 29–36.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar" authorityName="Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar" authorityYear="2021" box="[347,943,1677,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Spilomena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sahyadriensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[347,599,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Spilomena sahyadriensis</emphasis>
Tessy, Sureshan &amp; Girish Kumar
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[953,1034,1677,1701]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[953,1034,1677,1701]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, Holotype ♀. 29. Habitus, lateral view; 30. Head, frontal view; 31. Head and mesosoma (in part), dorsal view; 32. Mesosoma, lateral view; 33. Propodeum, dorsal view; 34. Metasoma, dorsal view; 35. Fore wing; 36. Hind wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1819,1990]" box="[199,1062,1819,1846]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1820,1846]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Integument shiny; T4–T7 with sparse setigerous micropunctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1819,1990]" box="[199,418,1855,1882]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1856,1882]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="272" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1819,1990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1892,1918]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a commemorative, genitive noun taken from patronym Tsuneki after late Dr. Katsuji Tsuneki, in honor of his immense contribution to aculeate hymenopteran taxonomy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
